Third Department,

May, 1959

(May 6, 1959) The People of the State of New York ex rel. Charles J. Wilkinson, Appellant, against Daniel McMann, as Warden of Clinton Prison, Respondent.

Motion for extension of time within which to perfect appeal. Motion granted and time within which to perfect appeal, file note of issue, and file and serve record and brief is extended until October 19, 1959 and the ease is to be ready for argument at the November Term of this court. Present — Foster, P. J., Bergan, Gibson, Herlihy and Reynolds, JJ.
